{
  "texts": [
    "The constant comparative analysis revealed three main themes that are described in the results section.",
    "Results General characteristics of the study population (Table 1)The study population (n = 217) was predominantly female (85.7%), with an average age of 26.9 ± 5.7 years (range 18-52 years).",
    "A total of 190 (82.3%) students were born in Israel, and more than 90% identified as Jewish, 4.6% as Muslim, and 0.5% as Christian.",
    "A significant proportion (65.4%) of the participants were either married or cohabiting.",
    "Geographically, the residential distribution of students was as follows: 43.9% in the Center of Israel, 18.9% in Northern Israel, 14.1% in the South, and 10.7% in Jerusalem."
  ]
}